{"object_id": "", "title": "\"Richard Kan Vase\"", "period": "Ca. 1350 – Yuan Dynasty (1279-1368)", "type": "", "material": "", "description": "This exceptional Chinese vase with its blue and white décor, dated to the mid-14thcentury, is a work crafted in China under the Yuan Dynasty (1279-1368), and long held in a French family.", "dimensions": "H. 42 cm", "museum": "Musée Guimet", "location": "Paris, France", "detail_url": "https://www.guimet.fr/en/our-collections/china/richard-kan-vase", "image_url": "https://www.guimet.fr/sites/default/files/styles/mosaic_list/public/2023-06/vase-mepining-amis-de-guimet.jpg?itok=Fd6yCUKW", "image_path": "", "credit_line": "", "accession_number": "", "crawl_date": "2026-05-27", "_category": "", "_image_valid": true}
{"object_id": "", "title": "Wedding headdress", "period": "Beginning of the 20th century", "type": "", "material": "", "description": "The wedding headdress known as the “phoenix tiara” was donned by the women of the Han ethnic group on the occasion of their wedding, as well as for the most formal occasions –, thus we often find them represented in portraits of ancestors.", "dimensions": "54 cm", "museum": "Musée Guimet", "location": "Paris, France", "detail_url": "https://www.guimet.fr/en/our-collections/china/wedding-headdress", "image_url": "https://www.guimet.fr/sites/default/files/styles/mosaic_list/public/2023-09/coiffe-nuptiale.jpg?itok=D2Z0yOex", "image_path": "", "credit_line": "", "accession_number": "", "crawl_date": "2026-05-27", "_category": "", "_image_valid": true}
{"object_id": "", "title": "Bowl with a wave decor", "period": "Yongzheng Era (1723-1735)", "type": "", "material": "", "description": "The originality of this bowl with its wave decoration is owed to the delicacy of the material and the bold graphism of the décor.", "dimensions": "6.2 cm", "museum": "Musée Guimet", "location": "Paris, France", "detail_url": "https://www.guimet.fr/en/our-collections/china/bowl-wave-decor", "image_url": "https://www.guimet.fr/sites/default/files/styles/mosaic_list/public/2023-09/bol-decor-vague.jpg?itok=FoxSgkeU", "image_path": "", "credit_line": "", "accession_number": "", "crawl_date": "2026-05-27", "_category": "", "_image_valid": true}
{"object_id": "", "title": "Pig-Dragon (zhulong)", "period": "4th millennium BC", "type": "", "material": "", "description": "Literally meaning “pig-dragon”, thezhulongis a magical creature formed by a serpentine body wrapped around an orifice, and ending with a pig’s head topped by two raised ears, a pair of round eyes, and a flat wrinkled snout.", "dimensions": "H: 15.3 cm", "museum": "Musée Guimet", "location": "Paris, France", "detail_url": "https://www.guimet.fr/en/our-collections/china/pig-dragon-zhulong", "image_url": "https://www.guimet.fr/sites/default/files/styles/mosaic_list/public/2023-10/dragon-cochon.jpg?itok=_1VD8S6W", "image_path": "", "credit_line": "", "accession_number": "", "crawl_date": "2026-05-27", "_category": "", "_image_valid": true}
